  <summary date="2004-03-19T21:36:32Z" status="Introduced in Senate">American Manufacturing Jobs Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to repeal the exclusion from gross income of extraterritorial income (gross income attributable to foreign trading gross receipts).

Allows a deduction equal to nine percent of the qualified domestic production activities income, up to 50 percent of the W-2 wages paid by the employer for the taxable year.</summary>
